uses and Romanesque churches dominating its many hillsides. The vineyard is planted on hillsides, plateaux and at the foot of the slopes. The soil can be Perigord sand or clay-limestone, producing wines which can be enjoyed young as well as those designed for long ageing.\r\n\r\nGood depth of ruby red. Nose: Aroma of black fruits. Palate: Well balanced with fresh fruit flavours and a hint of spice.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13%</li>\r\n 	<li>Lussac Saint  Emillion/ Bordeaux - France</li>\r\n</ul>','ROC DE LUSSAC - Lussac Saint Emilion','','publish','open','open','','roc-de-lussac-lussac-saint-emilion-2','','','2016-12-28 15:10:05','2016-12-28 08:10:05','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=563',0,'post','',0),(564,1,'2016-12-28 15:10:01','2016-12-28 08:10:01','The Lussac Saint-Emilion appellation is found to the north of the hill of Saint-Emilion. The first vineyard to be designated a World Heritage Site, the region is full of charm, with prestigious historic houses and Romanesque churches dominating its many hillsides. The vineyard is planted on hillsides, plateaux and at the foot of the slopes. The soil can be Perigord sand or clay-limestone, producing wines which can be enjoyed young as well as those designed for long ageing.\r\n\r\nGood depth of ruby red. Nose: Aroma of black fruits. Palate: Well balanced with fresh fruit flavours and a hint of spice.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13%</li>\r\n 	<li>Lussac Saint  Emillion/ Bordeaux - France</li>\r\n</ul>','ROC DE LUSSAC - Lussac Saint Emilion','','inherit','closed','closed','','563-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:10:01','2016-12-28 08:10:01','',563,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/564',0,'revision','',0),(565,1,'2016-12-28 15:10:31','2016-12-28 08:10:31','The Ollet-Fourreau family has owned different chteaux in the Bordeaux region for five generations. The vineyards of Chteau Haut Surget cover 35 hectares in the Lalande-de-Pomerol appellation. The terraced vineyards are spread over two villages. The soil consists of a mix of clay, gravel and even sand in the western part, near to the river. This soil type is ideal for Merlot, which is the major component in the blend. The Lalande-de-Pomerol appellation produces very elegant wines with a deep ruby-garnet colour, great subtlety, intense on the nose and perfectly balanced on the palate. They are very expressive on the nose, with red berry fruit aromas. Bright cherry red colour with good intensity. A full-bodied wine with a long finish.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13%</li>\r\n 	<li>Lalande De Pomerol/ Bordeaux - France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau HAUT - SURGET - Lalande De Pomerol','','inherit','closed','closed','','561-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:10:31','2016-12-28 08:10:31','',561,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/565',0,'revision','',0),(566,1,'2016-12-28 15:13:21','2016-12-28 08:13:21','Wines of the Bordeaux Suprieur appellation are produced the vineyard zone of the Gironde. The wines must conform to rigorous quality criteria and are made from grapes from selected vineyard parcels and older vines. The red Bordeaux Suprieur is characterized by great aromatic complexity combining ripe fruits, floral aromas, spice and often a hint of oak\r\n\r\nDeep ruby red colour. Nose of ripe red fruit aromas with a hint of oak. Full bodied with ripe tannins and a long finish.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux Superieur /France</li>\r\n</ul>','ARNOZAN BORDEAUX SUPERIEUR','','publish','open','open','','arnozan-bordeaux-superieur-2','','','2016-12-28 15:13:25','2016-12-28 08:13:25','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=566',0,'post','',0),(567,1,'2016-12-28 15:13:21','2016-12-28 08:13:21','Wines of the Bordeaux Suprieur appellation are produced the vineyard zone of the Gironde. The wines must conform to rigorous quality criteria and are made from grapes from selected vineyard parcels and older vines. The red Bordeaux Suprieur is characterized by great aromatic complexity combining ripe fruits, floral aromas, spice and often a hint of oak\r\n\r\nDeep ruby red colour. Nose of ripe red fruit aromas with a hint of oak. Full bodied with ripe tannins and a long finish.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux Superieur /France</li>\r\n</ul>','ARNOZAN BORDEAUX SUPERIEUR','','inherit','closed','closed','','566-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:13:21','2016-12-28 08:13:21','',566,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/567',0,'revision','',0),(568,1,'2016-12-28 15:14:55','2016-12-28 08:14:55','Bordeaux is the largest vineyard for appellation wines in the whole of France. The richness, the quality and the diversity of its wines derive from the particular character of the terroirs, the experience of the winegrowers and the art of blending. The tide, which flows up both of the region\'s rivers, brings very specific characteristics to the wines. With its huge size, Bordeaux reds offer an infinite palette of flavours and combine their qualities in myriad different ways.\r\n\r\nCherry red with good depth. Fresh and spicy nose with a hint of oak. Soft, silky tannins and well-rounded on the palate.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux /France</li>\r\n</ul>','ARNOZAN BORDEAUX','','publish','open','open','','arnozan-bordeaux-2','','','2016-12-28 15:15:00','2016-12-28 08:15:00','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=568',0,'post','',0),(569,1,'2016-12-28 15:14:55','2016-12-28 08:14:55','Bordeaux is the largest vineyard for appellation wines in the whole of France. The richness, the quality and the diversity of its wines derive from the particular character of the terroirs, the experience of the winegrowers and the art of blending. The tide, which flows up both of the region\'s rivers, brings very specific characteristics to the wines. With its huge size, Bordeaux reds offer an infinite palette of flavours and combine their qualities in myriad different ways.\r\n\r\nCherry red with good depth. Fresh and spicy nose with a hint of oak. Soft, silky tannins and well-rounded on the palate.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux /France</li>\r\n</ul>','ARNOZAN BORDEAUX','','inherit','closed','closed','','568-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:14:55','2016-12-28 08:14:55','',568,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/569',0,'revision','',0),(570,1,'2016-12-28 15:16:17','2016-12-28 08:16:17','The Abbey of La Sauve Majeure was founded in 1079 by the Duke of aquitaine ans Saint-Grard. This traditional Red Bordeaux opens with classic aromas of black fruits and sweet spices. The wine is elegantly balanced and medium-bodied on the palate. The finish shows fine vanilla notes.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux /France</li>\r\n</ul>','LAVERGNE BORDEAUX ROUGE','','publish','open','open','','lavergne-bordeaux-rouge-2','','','2016-12-28 15:16:20','2016-12-28 08:16:20','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=570',0,'post','',0),(571,1,'2016-12-28 15:16:17','2016-12-28 08:16:17','The Abbey of La Sauve Majeure was founded in 1079 by the Duke of aquitaine ans Saint-Grard. This traditional Red Bordeaux opens with classic aromas of black fruits and sweet spices. The wine is elegantly balanced and medium-bodied on the palate. The finish shows fine vanilla notes.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux /France</li>\r\n</ul>','LAVERGNE BORDEAUX ROUGE','','inherit','closed','closed','','570-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:16:17','2016-12-28 08:16:17','',570,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/571',0,'revision','',0),(572,1,'2016-12-28 15:17:39','2016-12-28 08:17:39','Dark and thick colour with nice bright highlights. The bouquet is powerful with lightly spiced red fruits aromas. The attack is generous and round with a mid-palate marked by ripe tannins. The finish is supple and quite long. This wine is well-balanced with a good breadth. located in the heart of Targon, 35 km South-East of Bordeaux. Its construction dates back to the 11th century and shows the passing of the several Bordeaux aristocratic families.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux /France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau VIEUX MANOIR','','publish','open','open','','chateau-vieux-manoir-2','','','2016-12-28 15:17:44','2016-12-28 08:17:44','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=572',0,'post','',0),(573,1,'2016-12-28 15:17:39','2016-12-28 08:17:39','Dark and thick colour with nice bright highlights. The bouquet is powerful with lightly spiced red fruits aromas. The attack is generous and round with a mid-palate marked by ripe tannins. The finish is supple and quite long. This wine is well-balanced with a good breadth. located in the heart of Targon, 35 km South-East of Bordeaux. Its construction dates back to the 11th century and shows the passing of the several Bordeaux aristocratic families.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux /France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau VIEUX MANOIR','','inherit','closed','closed','','572-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:17:39','2016-12-28 08:17:39','',572,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/573',0,'revision','',0),(574,1,'2016-12-28 15:19:41','2016-12-28 08:19:41','Chteau Lalne and its vineyard are located in the heart of the Bordeaux. Since 1845, this property has always been run by the same family; five generations of wine-growers have passed down an ancestral know-how. Beautiful purple colour with dark hints. The bouquet develops black fruits scents with roasting notes. The attack is supple and round giving way to a generous mid-palate enhanced by ripe and nicely woody tannins.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux Superieur /France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau LALENE CUVEE PRESTIGE','','publish','open','open','','chateau-lalene-cuvee-prestige-2','','','2016-12-28 15:19:44','2016-12-28 08:19:44','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=574',0,'post','',0),(575,1,'2016-12-28 15:19:41','2016-12-28 08:19:41','Chteau Lalne and its vineyard are located in the heart of the Bordeaux. Since 1845, this property has always been run by the same family; five generations of wine-growers have passed down an ancestral know-how. Beautiful purple colour with dark hints. The bouquet develops black fruits scents with roasting notes. The attack is supple and round giving way to a generous mid-palate enhanced by ripe and nicely woody tannins.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>12,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Bordeaux Superieur /France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau LALENE CUVEE PRESTIGE','','inherit','closed','closed','','574-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:19:41','2016-12-28 08:19:41','',574,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/575',0,'revision','',0),(576,1,'2016-12-28 15:21:42','2016-12-28 08:21:42','Chteau La Gravette Lacombe was listed by Cocks and Feret as from the very first edition in 1850, and then as a Bourgeois Growth in 1893 and 1908. The\r\n\r\n17th edition can boast of re-listing a Growth dating from the first! The frost of 1956 decimated the few acres of vines dating from just after the war. It benefits from all the technology and know-how of this latter. Dark and thick ruby red colour being a sign of youth and concentration of the fruit. The bouquet is intense and reveals nice stewed black fruits aromas mixed with spices and vanilla. Good length. This wine is characterized by a good structure and elegance, enhanced by round palate with ripe tannins and black cherry and vanilla hints.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Medoc /France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau LA GRAVETTE LACOMBE 2010 - CRU BOURGEOIS','','publish','open','open','','chateau-la-gravette-lacombe-2010-cru-bourgeois-2','','','2016-12-28 15:21:46','2016-12-28 08:21:46','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=576',0,'post','',0),(577,1,'2016-12-28 15:21:42','2016-12-28 08:21:42','Chteau La Gravette Lacombe was listed by Cocks and Feret as from the very first edition in 1850, and then as a Bourgeois Growth in 1893 and 1908. The\r\n\r\n17th edition can boast of re-listing a Growth dating from the first! The frost of 1956 decimated the few acres of vines dating from just after the war. It benefits from all the technology and know-how of this latter. Dark and thick ruby red colour being a sign of youth and concentration of the fruit. The bouquet is intense and reveals nice stewed black fruits aromas mixed with spices and vanilla. Good length. This wine is characterized by a good structure and elegance, enhanced by round palate with ripe tannins and black cherry and vanilla hints.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Medoc /France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau LA GRAVETTE LACOMBE 2010 - CRU BOURGEOIS','','inherit','closed','closed','','576-revision-v1','','','2016-12-28 15:21:42','2016-12-28 08:21:42','',576,'http://54.226.229.29/archives/577',0,'revision','',0),(578,1,'2016-12-28 15:23:05','2016-12-28 08:23:05','First references to Chteau Bel Air are found in the 15th century. The vineyard, facing the Gironde River, is located on a rich soil, which often gives generous character, headiness\r\n\r\nand good colour to the wine produced.\r\n\r\nThick and brilliant colour with garnet highlights. The bouquet is intense and reveals blackberry and blackcurrant aromas. In the mouth, the attack is round with a pleasant thread, generous and silky. The finish is persistent, on the fruit with wood and vanilla notes.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>750ml x 6</li>\r\n 	<li>Red</li>\r\n 	<li>13,5%</li>\r\n 	<li>Haut Medoc /France</li>\r\n</ul>','Chateau BEL AIR 2009 - CRU BOURGEOIS','','publish','open','open','','chateau-bel-air-2009-cru-bourgeois-2','','','2016-12-28 15:23:09','2016-12-28 08:23:09','',0,'http://54.226.229.29/?p=578',0,'post','',0),(579,1,'2016-12-28 15:23:05','201